AU  - Tang, Yuehua
AU  - Yao, Vincent
T1  - Corporate Climate Risk: Measurements and Responses
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhad094
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 6
SP  - 1778
EP  - 1830
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper conducts a textual analysis of earnings call transcripts to quantify climate risk exposure at the firm level. We construct dictionaries that measure physical and transition climate risks separately and identify firms that proactively respond to climate risks. Our validation analysis shows that our measures capture firm-level variations in respective climate risk exposure. Firms facing high transition risk, especially those that do not proactively respond, have been valued at a discount in recent years as aggregate investor attention to climate-related issues has been increasing. We document differences in how firms respond through investment, green innovation, and employment when facing high climate risk exposure.
Y2  - 7/9/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhad094
ER  - 



